{
  "bookId": "laozi-boshu",
  "num": 17,
  "title": "第十七章（知有）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "太上，下知有之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "亓次，親譽之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "亓次，畏之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "亓下，侮之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "信不足，案有不信。"
    },
    {
      "text": "猶呵，亓貴言也。"
    },
    {
      "text": "成功遂事，而百姓謂我自然。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "其德可見，恩惠可稱，故親愛而譽之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 17,
          "end": 18
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "設刑法以治之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "禁多令煩，不可歸誠，故欺侮之。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 8,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "君信不足於下，下則應之以不信，而欺其君也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 8,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "說太上之君，舉事猶，貴重於言，恐離道失自然也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂天下太平也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 13
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "百姓不知君上之德淳厚，反以為己自當然也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ],
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不能以無為居事，不言為教，立善行施，使下得親而譽之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 17,
          "end": 18
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不復能以恩仁令物，而賴威權也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 6,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不能法以正齊民，而以智治國，下知避之，其令不從，故曰，侮之也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 8,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "夫御體失性，則疾病生；輔物失真，則疵釁作。信不足焉，則有不信，此自然之道也。已處不足，非智之所齊也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 8,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "自然，其端兆不可得而見也，其意趣不可得而覩也，無物可以易其言，言必有應，故曰悠兮其貴言也。居無為之事，行不言之教，不以形立物，故功成事遂，而百姓不知其所以然也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
